{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"balm-feast-mica","description":"## Summary\nThe reconciler resolves a ticket's `assignee` to a Jira user on TWO divergent code paths, producing inconsistent results for the same input. An UPDATE strictly resolves the assignee (exact / unique-normalized accountId, else unassign); a CREATE sends the **raw** local string to ACLI/Jira with no resolution, so Jira fuzzy-matches or applies a project-default assignee. Same local value `\"joe\"` therefore yields different outcomes depending on path.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Local ticket with `assignee=\"joe\"` (not a unique Jira identity — e.g. 3 \"Joe\"s exist).\n2. **CREATE path** (new issue): reconcile creates the Jira issue. **Actual:** Jira assigns it to `joeoakhart@navapbc.com` (fuzzy/default fallback) — a *wrong* user.\n3. **UPDATE path** (already-bound, Jira unassigned): reconcile diffs assignee. **Actual:** `\"joe\"` is unmappable → issue left unassigned (and inbound later clears the local value).\n\n**Expected:** both paths apply the SAME resolution policy: resolve `\"joe\"` → unique accountId if one exists, otherwise leave unassigned — never silently mis-assign to a fuzzy/default user.\n\n## Root Cause\n- **CREATE does NOT validate.** `acli.py:297-298` extracts the raw assignee; `acli_cli_ops.py:241-243` (non-JSON) and `:367-368` (JSON) pass the raw string straight to ACLI. No `validate_assignee_exists` call. ACLI/Jira then fuzzy-resolves or defaults.\n- **UPDATE DOES validate.** `acli.py:347-349` calls `validate_assignee_exists()` before mutating; the diff resolver `outbound_differ.py:506-535` + `outbound_fields.py:372-390` map unmappable → unassign (`\"\"`). Strict matcher: `acli.py:517-606`.\n\n## Proposed Unification\nAdd ONE shared resolver consumed by both paths:\n- New `AcliClient.resolve_assignee_for_mutation(assignee, *, issue_key=None, project_key=None) -> (accountId|None, authoritative: bool)` that wraps `validate_assignee_exists` and classifies the outcome: resolved accountId; `AssigneeNotFoundError` → `(None, authoritative=True)` (definitively unmappable → unassign); transient/API error → `(None, authoritative=False)` (do NOT unassign — preserve, let next pass retry). Preserve the `(acct, authoritative)` tuple rather than collapsing to a bare string, so a transient REST failure never spuriously unassigns.\n- **CREATE** (`create_issue`, no issue key yet) resolves with `project_key=<project>`: resolved accountId → include in payload; unmappable → omit (leave unassigned); transient → omit (avoid mis-assign).\n- **UPDATE** (`update_issue`, has issue key) resolves with `issue_key=<key>` via the same method.\n- The diff-side `_assignee_resolver` collapses to a thin wrapper over the shared method (single source of truth).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] CREATE and UPDATE route assignee resolution through ONE shared method; identical input yields identical Jira outcome.\n- [ ] An ambiguous/unmappable assignee (e.g. `\"joe\"`) is left UNASSIGNED on both paths — never fuzzy-matched or defaulted to an unrelated user.\n- [ ] A uniquely-resolvable assignee (exact email/accountId/displayName, or unique normalized variant) is assigned identically on both paths.\n- [ ] Transient resolution failures do NOT unassign (authoritative=False is preserved end-to-end); only authoritative AssigneeNotFoundError unassigns.\n- [ ] CREATE uses project-scope resolution (no issue_key yet); `validate_assignee_exists` already accepts `project_key`.\n- [ ] Tests: CREATE+UPDATE parity for ambiguous, exact, unique-normalized, and transient-error cases.\n\n## Affected Files (initial)\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli.py` (`create_issue`, `update_issue`, new shared resolver, `validate_assignee_exists`)\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_cli_ops.py` (CREATE raw-string call sites)\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py` / `outbound_fields.py` (diff resolver → wrapper)","id":"544e-0a25-eabb-4220","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Unify assignee resolution across CREATE and UPDATE reconciler paths (CREATE bypasses validate_assignee_exists -> fuzzy/default mis-assignment)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782753319449326001,"uuid":"49f30411-d672-4a81-b90d-3e5b3c7f9f9d"}